			<p><strong><span class="smallcaps">Andrew Boyd</span></strong> is the author of <em>Daily Afflictions</em> and <em>Life&rsquo;s Little Deconstruction Book</em> and is finishing work on <em>Pilgrimage to Nowhere</em>, his travelogue of a skeptic&rsquo;s spiritual journey around the world. When he&rsquo;s not writing, he&rsquo;s failing to save the Republic from itself: he cofounded Agit-Pop Communications, an award-winning &ldquo;subvertising&rdquo; agency, and for a decade led the satirical media campaign Billionaires for Bush. He lives in New York City.</p><a href="/contributors/andrew-boyd" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
